Analyze Your Data
Salesforce Analytics Tools
Reports and Dashboards
Manage Your Reports and Dashboards on Analytics Home
Reports
Create a Joined Report
With up to five blocks, joined reports let you view different types of information in a single report. Each block shows data from one standard or custom report type.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: both Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
Available in: Enhanced Folder Sharing

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create, edit, and delete joined reports:
Enhanced Folder Sharing
Create and Customize Reports
AND
Report Builder

You can turn any existing report into a joined report, or start fresh with a new one.

Create a Joined Report
The principal report type determines how common fields shared by different report types in a report are named.
Click Report | Joined Report | Apply.
Add another report type to the joined report: click Add Block. Choose a report type and customize the block after adding it.

Work with Blocks. 
Customize the joined report with columns, groups, filters, and formulas.
Save and name the report.
Optionally, describe the report and choose a report folder.
Click Save. To run the report, click Run.

Create a Joined Report in Salesforce Classic
Choose a report type and create it. The principal report type determines how common fields shared by different report types in a report are named.
Click Tabular Format  | Joined.
Add another report type: click Add Report Type. Choose a report type.
Customize the joined report with columns, groups, filters, and formulas.
Save and name the report.
Optionally, describe the report and choose a report folder.
Click Save. To run the report, click Run.
